<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="5653" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="5653">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="5653">White, small, elongated, costae of approximately 23 in number at the last whorl, with sharply spine at the shoulder, clearly spiral cords between costae, without umbilicus (Fig. 1c). Shell height 22.2mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="5653" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="5653">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="5653">Occurs in the Pacific coast off Sagami Bay to Kii Peninsula at 100m deep. In Taiwan it was dredged at about 500m depth of NE Taiwan waters. This species is a new record from the Taiwan waters.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
